# wikidata_cache.json — the big (~54 MB and growing) resumable SPARQL/entity cache.
# NOT committed: it's rebuildable from scratch (keyless Wikidata, a few minutes) and the
# ENRICHED OUTPUTS that the site actually needs (art_data.js, museum_highlights.js,
# palette.js) ARE committed. Keeping it local stops the repo bloating one blob per fold.
# highlights_cache.json (116 KB) + palette_cache.json (16 KB) stay committed — small, and
# they save the pricier per-museum / image passes across machines.
wikidata_cache.json
edge-tmp*/

# match_decisions.json — the artwork-detection side project's raw verdicts (photo filenames +
# lat/lon location history + per-photo match picks). Local-only PII; only the DERIVED, verified
# fields (qid, seenAt, seenConfidence, favorite) flow into the committed artworks.js.
match_decisions.json
